English:
The grocers are divided into two categories: the relatively small, with a population of between 5-7 million. They are composed mostly of cities and their respective districts. Some of them--Shenzhen, Shanghai, Dalian, Tianjin, Shenyang, Xiamen, Qingdao, and Suzhou--grow 15-20% faster than the Asian Tiger states of Malaysia, Taiwan, Thailand, and Korea have before. These smaller regional states are propelling growth in the larger regions, each with populations of between 100 million.
