English:
Weakly removed from the Left’s sphere of legitimate concern, Livni is self-consciously committed to the belief in Israel’s basic existence. Yet she is willing to come into contact with pragmatic Palestinians and offer them unfettered sovereignty against unfettered peace. She will not allow Palestinians to re-emigrate to Israel (which is controversially called “right of return”), but land is not hers. And she is offering little hope, an open horizon, and an unavoidable reality to Jews and Arabs.
