English:
Inner pressure on the Saudi King Family Al Saud arises from the widespread rejection of both war against Iraq and American military presence. Dissent comes not only from the streets, but also from the ranks of the religious establishment, the Wahhabis, who are Saudi Arabia’s oldest allies and guarantee their legitimacy. External pressure arises mainly from the US, Saudi Arabia’s largest strategic protector.
