English:
First, because some countries are more targeted at Europe for help. People and governments in sub-Saharan Africa or the Middle East are more prone – for political, historical, or cultural reasons – to seeking help in Europe, rather than in NATO. Some long-term crises, such as those arising from terrorism, are in Europe for which NATO is better suited. Conversely, there are some long-term crises, such as those involving terrorism, for which NATO is better suited.
German:
