English:
When Putin was elected president in 2000, he named World Trade Organization membership as his foreign policy priority. He failed because he gave in to small protectionist interests, including a wood embargo against Finland and Sweden, a fish embargo against Norway, and various agricultural embargoes against Lithuania, which engulfed Ukraine, Moldova, Georgia, and others.
