English:
While in 1978 there were only 186 newspapers and a half dozen magazines and radio stations, today China has roughly 2200 newspapers, 9,000 magazines, 1000 radio stations, and 420 television stations, and a growing number of cable television stations. Most of these radio stations rely on advertising revenues to finance their operations and growth.
German:
