Our capital markets are sufficiently sophisticated and deep to provide a lot of options for most large corporations to raise capital. Public markets aren’t the only option for smaller companies and individuals. They’re the ones that banks need most. They’re the ones that banks need most. I think they’re the ones that banks need most.
