English:
TOLEDO – Israel’s problem with the report by Judge Richard Goldstone, who accused the country of war crimes in the Gaza Strip, and the subsequent Billing of the report by the United Nations Human Rights Council recalls US Vice President Spiro Agnew’s response to the report in 1973, which was cited for corruption: “The Bastard – they have changed the rules without saying anything.”
German:
Vielleicht glauben einige europäische Führer tatsächlich, die Aufrechterhaltung des behaglichen Wohlstands der Union rechtfertige unser Schweigen zu Menschenrechten und anderen Themen, die dem Kreml lästig sind.
