English:
Even though implementation will be a long struggle, with some hefty resistance, central reforms are already under way. The current 12th Five-Year Plan calls for annual wage increases of at least 13.4% per annum; this year, wages are rising by an average of 18%, which will lead to the deprivation of some of the most powerful industries, such as the oil sector, and weaken their opposition to reform. The state campaign to combat corruption is targeting some of the most powerful industries, such as the oil sector.
German:
