China beispielsweise ist schon besorgt, dass diese Anreize der Fed seine Inflation in die Höhe treiben wird.
English:
With falling house prices (which will go even further down) and banks in a dire financial position, lenders lend nothing and households borrow nothing. While the additional liquidity pumped into the financial system by the Fed may have provided a financial shield, it will not stimulate consumption or investment. Instead, much of it will find its way into the foreign market. China, for example, is already worried that these Fed incentives will drive up inflation.
