English:
The remedy for the US deficit emerges immediately from this diagnosis: restore work through fiscal stimulus programs that end sinister wars, limit the costs of military and drugs, and raise taxes, at least for the super-rich. But the right wants nothing to do with this, and instead is lobbying for more tax cuts for the big business and the wealthy, and for investment and social protection that threaten the US economy’s future viability and sever the social contract’s remnants. Meanwhile, the US financial sector is lobbying hard to be free of existing regulations in order to return to its earlier disastrous easy behavior.
