Als Moore 1984 entdeckte, daß er Patient Nr. 4.438.032 geworden war, klagte er auf Amtsmißbrauch und Eigentumsdiebstahl.
Sein Arzt machte geltend, Moore habe sein Interesse an Körperteilen dadurch abgetreten, daß er eine allgemeine Einverständniserklärung unterschrieben habe.
Aber Moore sah sich in seiner Integrität verletzt und glaubte sein Körper sei ausbeutete und sein Gewebe zu Erzeugnissen weiter verarbeit worden.
English:
Moore became suspicious when cancer specialists at UCLA’s clinic repeated for seven years to take samples of his blood, bone marrow, skin, and sperm. When Moore discovered in 1984 that he was patient number 4.438.032, he sued for office privilege and property damage. His physician claimed that Moore had waived his interest in body parts by signing a general agreement. But Moore felt violated in his integrity and allowed his body to be exploited and his tissue to be produced.
German:
