Doch hatten die alten Griechen die Naturphilosophie, und die alten Römer glaubten daran, herauszufinden, was funktionierte, und es anzuwenden.
Alles aber, was sie hervorbrachten, waren einige herausragende architektonische Werke, Infrastruktur und ein militärisches Ausbildungssystem, das ihre Gesellschaft über den Mittelmeerraum hinaus ausbreitete.
English:
Some say it was the Entzaubering of the World, a shift from a worldview based on prayer and reconciliation of spirits to a reliance on rational manipulation and management of nature and society. But the ancient Greeks had the natural philosophy, and the ancient Romans believed in figuring out what worked and how to apply it. Yet what they produced were some outstanding architectural works, infrastructure, and a military education system that extended their society beyond the Mediterranean.
