English:
The ability to combine operating system and software made life much easier for ordinary users. They got just about everything they wanted (and probably much more) when buying a computer. But the possibility of choosing and combining different software was reduced. Microsoft’s critics have complained unabated about this, claiming that the integration of the browser into the operating system per se drew out superior software solutions.
German:
