English:
Many observers say that leadership is more a art than a science. Good leadership is situational. In my book The Powers to Lead, I call this ability “contextual intelligence.” The ability to mobilize a group successfully is certainly more a art than a predictor science, and situation to situation is different, which does not mean that it cannot be usefully studied and learned.
