All the more important is that leaders in the US and Europe are beginning to take capital from the anti-globalist movement. The scandals in American firms undermined the market’s moral position, while the end of the Internet bubble has weakened its economic credibility. The weakened distributional effects on market-oriented financing may serve to strengthen market forces in Europe, particularly in southern Europe.
