Ein westafrikanisches Land, in dem man Ölreserven gefunden hat, muss Erkundungen, Bohrungen und den Bau von Pipelines finanzieren. Das heißt, dass es sich über einen Zeithorizont von 10 bis 20 Jahren absichern muss und nicht nur über 90 Tage.
English:
One alternative for some commodity exporters is to hedge risk by buying futures markets. But a significant disadvantage of derivatives is their short maturity. A West African country that has found oil reserves needs to finance reserves, drilling, and pipeline construction over a 10--20-year period, not just 90 days. The maturity of the pipelines, then, is a 10-20-year period. But the country that needs to hedge its risk over a 10--20-year period needs to finance exploration, drilling, and pipeline construction.
