English:
What could have caused the glacier to have stopped? One factor could be snow accumulations of dust and debris (which fall under the smelting action of “aerosole”), which can greatly increase the melting rate at 400 Grams per square meter. Nevertheless, if the accumulations exceed 600 Grams, the melting rate could be stopped if the snow accumulations are not stopped.
