English:
Foremost among this new generation of revisionist historians was Harvard University’s Niall Ferguson, whose television series following his new book Civilization: The West and the Rest is now in the United Kingdom. In the first episode, Ferguson appears with the petty Denkmälers of China’s Ming Dynasty, which in 15th-century China was undoubtedly the largest civilization of their time, on the seaward to Africa. From that point on, it was only downhill for China (and “the Rest”) and for the West.
