English:
Sometimes the climate debate appears very complicated: one threatens to drown in a sea of acronyms; the number of proposed technical patent solutions grows; and the experts argue over the right price of carbon and appropriate discount rates. But the complexity is all about a simple truth: for a decade or more we have known about the risk of further climate emissions, yet we have completely failed to take credible steps to end them.
